  schema:name "Brassica juncea" ;
  schema:description "Annual from Brassicaceae, native to Central Asia. Produces large, wrinkled leaves with elevated glucosinolate and volatile sulfur content compared to *B. oleracea*. Develops acrid, peppery flavor; bolts rapidly in heat. Primary use as quick-maturing spring and fall green crop in temperate climates." ;
